{"question_id": "2016_B_19", "source": {"exam": "NSAA", "year": 2016, "paper": "Part B Physics", "section": "B", "question_number": 19, "page": 15, "source_pdf": "raw/2016.pdf"}, "content": {"subject": "physics", "topic": null, "subtopic": null, "archetype": null, "difficulty": 2, "requires_diagram": false, "requires_calculation": false}, "prompt": {"stem": "In the 1920s scientists discovered that the universe is expanding. One consequence of this expansion is that intense gamma-ray radiation from the early universe has now been shifted to the microwave region of the electromagnetic spectrum.

