The power currently radiated by the Sun is $4.0 \times 10^{26}$ W. Towards the end of the Sun's life its radius will increase by a factor of 100 and its surface temperature will decrease by a factor of 2.

What will be the power radiated by the Sun when these changes have occurred?", "options": [{"label": "A", "text": "$2.5 \times 10^{27}$ W"}, {"label": "B", "text": "$1.0 \times 10^{28}$ W"}, {"label": "C", "text": "$2.0 \times 10^{28}$ W"}, {"label": "D", "text": "$2.5 \times 10^{29}$ W"}, {"label": "E", "text": "$1.0 \times 10^{30}$ W"}, {"label": "F", "text": "$2.0 \times 10^{30}$ W"}, {"label": "G", "text": "$2.5 \times 10^{33}$ W"}, {"label": "H", "text": "$1.0 \times 10^{34}$ W"}], "figures": []}, "generation": {"template_id": "physics_q026", "template_version": "1.0", "parameters": {}, "solution_steps": [], "distractor_strategy": []}, "validation": {"answer_label": "D", "answer_text": "$2.5 \times 10^{29}$ W", "status": "verified"}, "metadata": {"estimated_time_seconds": null, "tags": ["physics"]}, "data_quality_notes": []}

